  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|image = Beefalo Wool Dropped.png\n|icon = Beefalo Wool.png\n|craft_desctiption = ''Transmute Beard Hair into Beefalo Wool.''\n|burnTime = [[File:Light_Sources_Filter.png|32px|link=Fuel#Fire Fuel]] 45 sec.\n|stack = 40\n|droppedBy = {{pic|32|Beefalo}} (&times;3), {{pic|32|Baby Beefalo}} (&times;1 as Baby, &times;2 as Toddler and Teen) {{pic|24|Tumbleweed}} (1% &times;3)\n|spawnCode = \"beefalowool\"\n|filter = {{Pic32|Wilson Filter}}\n|canBeBurned=1\n|ingredient1 = Beard Hair\n|multiplier1 = 2 ({{Pic|28|Wilson Portrait|Wilson}} only)\n|skill = Transmute Icky II\n|skillOwner = Wilson\n}}\n{{Quotes\n|wolfgang=I make clothes of hair-cow.\n|wilson=It smells like beefalo tears.\n|willow=Ha! I stole his hair!\n|woodie=It feels like my beard.\n|maxwell=It smells like a barn.\n|wagstaff=Radiating a musty smell.\n|wendy=Somewhere, a beefalo is naked and cold.\n|woodlegs=Carries a musk wit' it.\n|wickerbottom=Long follicles harvested from the beefalo.\n|webber=Thick fur.\n|warly=The beast's loss is my gain.\n|wx78=EXTRUDED BEEFALO DISGUSTINGNESS\n|walani=It looks more like hair to me.\n|wigfrid=I d枚 l枚ve w枚olly things.\n|wilba = WOOL FROM ANY OTHER BEAST WOULD SMELL SWEETER\n|wormwood = Buddy hair\n|wheeler = A woolly projectile.\n|winona = Smelly, but warm.\n|wortox = Ex-beefalo\n|wurt = Fluffs.\n|walter = Sorry, beefalo.\n|wanda = The beefalo will grow it back.\n|choose=maxwell}}\n'''Beefalo Wool''' is an [[Item]] obtained by killing a [[Beefalo]] or聽a聽[[Baby Beefalo]], by shaving a [[sleeping]]聽Beefalo with a [[Razor]] (by clicking them with a Razor held by the mouse cursor), or using a [[Brush]] on a Beefalo.聽It is used to make a [[Saddle]], [[Winter Hat]], [[Beefalo Hat]], [[Puffy Vest]], and [[Carpeted Flooring]].\n\nBeefalo Wool also makes an excellent [[Fuel]] source for [[Campfire]]s and Fire Pits. A small herd of Beefalo can easily keep a Fire Pit lit for days, and as the wool grows back, this is a good short term solution.\nThere are alternative methods of obtaining Beefalo Wool; harvesting a [[Tumbleweed]], or befriending a [[Catcoon]], as friendly Catcoons may give Beefalo Wool as a gift.\n\n[[Willow]] needs Beefalo Wool to craft [[Bernie]]. It is also required to craft [[Lures|Spinnerbait Lures]] and to complete the construction of the [[Royal Tapestry]].\n\nBeefalo Wool can be crafted by Wilson if he got \"[[Transmute Icky II]]\"\n\n=={{pic|32|Icon Tools}} Usage==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Pig Skin\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Gold Nugget\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Saddle}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Silk\n|count2 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Winter Hat}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 8\n|item2 = Beefalo Horn\n|tool = Science Machine\n|result = Beefalo Hat}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Silk\n|count2 = 8\n|item3 = Winter Koalefant Trunk\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Puffy Vest}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|item2 = Boards\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Carpeted Flooring\n|resultcount = 4}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|item2 = Boards\n|result = Lush Carpet\n|resultcount = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item2 = Boards\n|count2 = 4\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 2\n|result = Beefalo Grooming Station\n|tool = Alchemy Engine}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 1\n|item2 = Flint\n|count2 = 1\n|item3 = Red Cap\n|result = Sunrise Spinnerbait\n|tool = Tackle Receptacle}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 1\n|item2 = Flint\n|count2 = 1\n|item3 = Green Cap\n|result = Dusky Spinnerbait\n|tool = Tackle Receptacle}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 1\n|item2 = Flint\n|count2 = 1\n|item3 = Blue Cap\n|result = Nightflyer Spinnerbait\n|tool = Tackle Receptacle}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Beefalo Wool\n|count1 = 5\n|item2 = Pig Skin\n|count2 = 3\n|item3 = Desert Stone\n|count3 = 1\n